WEBVTT

00:08.384 --> 00:11.046
-What the hell are you doing here?
-Nothing. Sleeping.

00:11.220 --> 00:13.597
-Did you touch me?
-Hell no, I swear.

00:14.098 --> 00:17.181
Sookie, listen. Bill asked me
to look after you while he was away.

00:17.351 --> 00:20.263
-Did he ask you to do it buck-naked?
-No,no.

00:20.438 --> 00:23.601
-I want you out of here. Now.
-Listen, listen, Sookie.

00:23.774 --> 00:27.483
I need to tell you something about me,
something I've never told another person.

00:27.653 --> 00:31.237
Oh, my God, it's you.
You're the murderer.

00:31.407 --> 00:34.774
-No, no, Sookie--
-Oh, my God, you killed my grandmother.

01:04.357 --> 01:06.143
I'm not the killer, I swear.

01:07.693 --> 01:09.604
I'm a shape-shifter.

01:12.240 --> 01:14.777
Shut the fuck up.

02:51.172 --> 02:52.958
What's that for?

02:53.924 --> 02:56.381
-Give me your hand.
-Why?

02:56.552 --> 02:59.635
"Why, why, why?
Why's it have to be in the woods?

02:59.805 --> 03:04.674
Why's it have to be before dawn?
Why 799.95?

03:04.852 --> 03:06.808
Why, why, why?"

03:06.979 --> 03:10.096
You think knowing the answers
will save you?

03:10.274 --> 03:12.105
Shut up and give me your hand.

03:14.278 --> 03:15.609
You nasty bitch.

03:15.780 --> 03:19.238
That's cleaner than anything
you've ever touched.

03:21.869 --> 03:25.202
Hold it over the fire. Keep it there.

03:27.124 --> 03:30.241
Angelica root and spit.

03:31.045 --> 03:38.008
A lot stronger than holy water.
You got poison oozing out your pores.

03:38.344 --> 03:41.336
-You live near a highway?
-No.

03:41.514 --> 03:43.800
Cook with a microwave
or talk on a cell phone?

03:43.974 --> 03:46.716
-Who doesn't?
-I don't.

03:46.977 --> 03:51.220
All that pollution and technology,
that's how demons travel.

03:51.482 --> 03:57.102
That's why I stay away out here
in the woods, away from civilization.

03:57.863 --> 04:01.151
-Rub it on your face.
-Are you serious?

04:01.450 --> 04:04.157
You make sure to get around your eyes.

04:04.328 --> 04:07.491
That's the demon's doon/vays.

04:14.046 --> 04:15.502
Drink.

04:22.096 --> 04:24.712
-Jesus, what the hell is it?
-Snake juice.

04:24.890 --> 04:26.505
-lt's made from snakes?
-No.

04:26.684 --> 04:32.304
It snakes down in you,
coils around that evil and rips it out.

04:32.481 --> 04:36.474
All of it. Every last drop.

04:49.832 --> 04:51.322
-Jason?
-If I were you...

04:51.500 --> 04:53.877
...l'd get my filthy mind off of him.

04:55.254 --> 04:57.540
What is it that you vampires say?

04:57.715 --> 04:59.205
"Jason is mine."

05:00.509 --> 05:04.218
It's not like that. He's a good person.

05:04.388 --> 05:07.755
-Are you implying that I'm not?
-Well....

05:07.933 --> 05:11.596
Jason isn't planning to kill me
after I'm no longer any use to him.

05:11.770 --> 05:15.103
Sophomore year of college, I walked away
from an academic scholarship...

05:15.274 --> 05:20.394
...so I could go to this Guatemalan village,
help build their first irrigation system...

05:20.571 --> 05:23.938
...so they could have fresh water,
crops that didn't give them dysentery.

05:24.116 --> 05:28.029
So don't you dare
get morally superior on me.

05:28.204 --> 05:32.197
I am an organic vegan,
and my carbon footprint is miniscule.

05:33.000 --> 05:37.369
Because I know that, ultimately,
we're all just a single living being.

05:38.047 --> 05:40.038
But you are not.

05:41.050 --> 05:44.213
-What the hell?
-You got a clot forming.

05:45.763 --> 05:47.094
There.

05:49.433 --> 05:54.018
Okay, I need tape
to keep it at that angle.

06:03.280 --> 06:05.111
Jason,Jason,Jason.

06:06.617 --> 06:09.279
l was half dead. He only tried to help.

06:09.453 --> 06:13.196
He should've told me about this.
Why wouldn't he tell me about this?

06:13.374 --> 06:15.160
I won't tell him if you won't.

06:15.334 --> 06:19.247
Withholding is tantamount to lying,
and I can't have that in our relationship.

06:19.421 --> 06:21.798
This is so beneath us.

06:22.258 --> 06:27.218
Jason loves you.
He never cared about anyone before.

06:27.721 --> 06:32.636
-He even thinks that you might be the one.
-You talk about me with him?

06:35.229 --> 06:38.972
And he said that? He said that
he thinks that I might be the one?

06:39.149 --> 06:44.644
Amy, if I die here,
Jason will never forgive you...

06:44.822 --> 06:46.983
...even if he wanted to.

06:47.157 --> 06:51.400
-He's not as evolved as you are.
-I know.

06:53.664 --> 06:54.870
A shape-shifter?

06:55.332 --> 06:57.709
Most of us refer to ourselves
simply as shifters.

06:57.876 --> 07:00.083
Well, how many of you are there?

07:00.879 --> 07:04.997
Thousands, tens of thousands, maybe.
We don't exactly have a newsletter.

07:05.175 --> 07:08.133
Do you come from, like,
a family of shifters or something?

07:08.304 --> 07:12.217
lt's hereditary, so yeah, I suppose.

07:13.559 --> 07:17.472
But...l was adopted.

07:18.230 --> 07:21.188
And the family that took me in....

07:22.776 --> 07:24.892
We just never talked about it.

07:26.447 --> 07:29.655
Can you turn into anything,
like cats, birds?

07:29.825 --> 07:31.611
Cats, sure.

07:32.453 --> 07:35.411
Yeah, I can do bird, but flying's hard.

07:36.540 --> 07:38.952
Dog's the easiest for me.

07:39.126 --> 07:42.869
People like dogs.
Most other animals leave you alone.

07:43.047 --> 07:47.290
| used to scratch your belly
in the parking lot at the bar.

07:48.802 --> 07:51.384
That wasn't me, that was a real dog.

07:52.139 --> 07:58.055
I need a live animal in order to shift.
You know, as a model.

07:58.562 --> 08:03.397
-Kind of like an imprint.
-Can you turn into another person?

08:06.111 --> 08:11.526
Humans are too complex.
Despite what you might see at the bar.

08:12.242 --> 08:16.736
-Can you do it any time, or what?
-Yeah.

08:17.247 --> 08:20.410
Yeah, but it wears off if I fall asleep.

08:20.584 --> 08:22.950
And on a full moon,
I can't stop the shift.

08:23.128 --> 08:26.712
-Like a werewolf.
-We're not werewolves.

08:27.466 --> 08:30.333
Hey, werewolves are dangerous,
nasty creatures.

08:30.511 --> 08:32.251
Do not call me a werewolf.

08:33.389 --> 08:35.095
Werewolves exist too?

08:42.272 --> 08:43.603
What else is there?

08:47.778 --> 08:50.520
More than you could imagine.

09:10.092 --> 09:11.673
I can't....

09:13.095 --> 09:16.553
Life is just getting too weird, too fast.

09:19.268 --> 09:21.259
Could a werewolf have killed Gran?

09:23.564 --> 09:26.180
I suppose it's possible.

09:27.317 --> 09:29.774
Oh, my God.
Bill's been dragged off by vampires...

09:29.945 --> 09:32.937
...and now | find out you're something
I never even knew existed.

09:41.790 --> 09:43.030
Don't!

09:46.837 --> 09:50.671
-I thought you would understand.
-Why? Because I'm dating a vampire?

09:50.841 --> 09:54.129
-You know what it's like to live with a secret.
-I don't hide who I am.

09:56.221 --> 09:59.088
I've wanted to tell you for years.

09:59.558 --> 10:01.549
I kissed you.

10:01.727 --> 10:04.639
And I know
you wanted to do more than that.

10:04.855 --> 10:07.767
Were you gonna tell me before or after?

10:15.949 --> 10:20.693
Spit, smoke, root.

10:21.371 --> 10:23.908
Cleanse the body.

10:24.208 --> 10:27.416
Cleanse the soul.

10:27.669 --> 10:32.379
Snake, seek, search, find.

10:33.217 --> 10:35.424
Bring it to the light.

10:36.136 --> 10:38.377
The light.

10:39.848 --> 10:44.387
-Fuck, my stomach.
-lt's angry.

10:44.561 --> 10:48.804
lt's digging its claws so it can hold on.
Don't you fight back.

10:48.982 --> 10:52.065
Let your body be the battleground.

10:52.236 --> 10:54.852
You let that demon destroy itself.

10:56.073 --> 10:59.190
-| feel sick.
-Let it go, let it go.

10:59.368 --> 11:02.405
Let it go. Let go of all that sickness...

11:02.579 --> 11:08.199
...all that rage, all that anger,
all that hate, all that self-pity.

11:08.377 --> 11:11.835
It's just fuel for the demon inside of you.

11:12.005 --> 11:13.256
Fuck.

11:19.304 --> 11:23.468
Come forth, demon.
Leave this child in peace.

11:23.642 --> 11:28.261
Come into the light. Show yourself.

11:31.942 --> 11:34.979
-That ain't real.
-What's there?

11:36.113 --> 11:38.104
Tell me what you see.

11:38.949 --> 11:42.282
It's me standing right over there.

11:43.078 --> 11:44.443
It's me.

11:44.621 --> 11:47.363
The demon will take on any form
to stay alive.

11:47.541 --> 11:51.750
It knows your weaknesses.
It preys on your fears.

11:53.839 --> 11:56.125
Only you can destroy it.

12:20.824 --> 12:24.487
-No, Mama, please, don't hurt me.
-One of you must die.

12:41.720 --> 12:45.679
Good girl. Good girl, good girl.

12:45.849 --> 12:49.683
Good girl. It's all over now.

12:50.646 --> 12:54.685
That demon is gone forever.

12:57.778 --> 13:00.565
You spend more time on your hair
than any man I've ever met.

13:00.739 --> 13:03.401
The trick is to make it look like
you didn't do nothing.

13:03.575 --> 13:05.236
It's harder than it might seem.

13:05.410 --> 13:08.402
I don't think you need
any help looking good, you know it.

13:08.580 --> 13:11.572
I think I might have had
one too many beers last night.

13:11.750 --> 13:15.242
| feel like I been shot at and missed,
shit at and hit.

13:18.215 --> 13:20.251
We need to talk about Eddie.

13:20.884 --> 13:23.591
-Okay.
-Well, I've been thinking.

13:23.762 --> 13:27.596
The way that we've been treating him,
it's just really uncivilized, you know?

13:27.766 --> 13:29.973
Yeah. I do know.

13:30.143 --> 13:31.974
We can't let him go, of course...

13:32.145 --> 13:36.730
...but we can try to make things
just a little bit more comfortable for him.

13:36.900 --> 13:39.562
Do you know what
Stockholm syndrome is?

13:40.028 --> 13:42.485
It's a disease.

13:42.906 --> 13:46.239
Not exactly. It's something
that happens to people who are kidnapped.

13:46.410 --> 13:50.244
It's like, over time, they start
to get closer to their kidnappers.

13:50.414 --> 13:53.747
It's kind of like being part of a family.

13:53.917 --> 13:57.876
-Really?
-All we need to do is make Eddie love us.

14:00.090 --> 14:02.752
And eventually,
we wouldn't have to keep him locked up.

14:02.926 --> 14:05.338
He could just be in the house with us,
like he's--

14:05.512 --> 14:06.922
-Like a pet.
-Yeah.

14:07.097 --> 14:08.928
-And we could travel with him.
-Yeah.

14:09.099 --> 14:11.135
We could sell his blood
when we need money.

14:11.309 --> 14:14.016
And just live out of backpacks
and see the whole world.

14:14.187 --> 14:15.802
We just need boots and a map.

14:16.690 --> 14:19.602
-I ain't never seen snow.
-Tibet.

14:19.776 --> 14:22.984
We can climb the Himalayas.
We can visit the Dalai Lama.

14:23.155 --> 14:24.941
And snowboard naked.

14:25.115 --> 14:28.278
Right, I gotta go to the store.
I wanna get Eddie some Tru Bloods.

14:28.452 --> 14:30.408
Really?

14:30.954 --> 14:32.569
I love you.

14:36.960 --> 14:39.497
-I love you too.
-I love you more.

14:43.925 --> 14:45.506
Oh, my God.

14:46.261 --> 14:49.298
You are even better looking
than you were yesterday.

14:55.645 --> 14:59.183
Mama. Mama, wake up.

15:01.151 --> 15:03.107
Baby, where you been?
I've been so worried.

15:03.278 --> 15:04.984
I had the exorcism.

15:08.158 --> 15:09.614
Tara, are you...?

15:10.494 --> 15:13.827
It worked, Mama. It worked.

15:13.997 --> 15:18.206
Jesus answered my prayers.
We're saved.

15:20.295 --> 15:25.835
Both of us, saved.
You did a brave thing, Tara Mae.

15:26.343 --> 15:28.675
I am so proud of you, my baby.

15:28.845 --> 15:33.509
My whole life, I thought you didn't....
I thought--

15:36.019 --> 15:37.850
I forgive you.

15:39.272 --> 15:42.014
Get dressed.
I'm taking you out to celebrate.

15:42.192 --> 15:44.774
Anywhere you wanna go.

15:46.238 --> 15:48.320
How about Mamaw's Mudbugs
over in Keachi?

15:48.490 --> 15:50.606
-That too far to drive to?
-Are you kidding?

15:50.784 --> 15:52.320
I'd drive anywhere for you.

16:02.546 --> 16:05.379
Sookie, could you reach me up
another box of paper lanterns?

16:05.549 --> 16:08.791
I'm kind of busy right now
setting up your bar.

16:09.219 --> 16:12.586
Thank you, Terry.
You are so sweet and reliable.

16:12.764 --> 16:16.507
I always know what to expect from you.
No nasty surprises.

16:16.685 --> 16:19.392
That's just because
you don't know me very well.

16:22.065 --> 16:26.900
Oh, Sam.
These lanterns are just precious.

16:28.071 --> 16:31.313
But they ought to alternate colors.
Like boy-girl seating.

16:31.491 --> 16:33.231
But they're already in place.

16:33.410 --> 16:36.117
-Oh, it won't take a minute to change.
-All right, Arlene.

16:36.288 --> 16:39.906
Don't you think they should hang
in little scallops, like a gingerbread house?

16:40.083 --> 16:45.498
It'll be more romantic that way,
not like some hick barn dance.

16:45.672 --> 16:48.584
-What do you want it to look like?
-A debutante ball.

16:48.758 --> 16:52.421
Hug your neck.
You know exactly what I'm talking about.

16:52.596 --> 16:55.178
I'll be right back. Thank you, Sam.

16:55.599 --> 16:57.135
How did you know what she wanted?

16:57.309 --> 17:00.847
My cousin Portia was a deb in Shreveport
when she turned 18.

17:01.021 --> 17:02.932
Every Bellefleur woman's been doing it...

17:03.106 --> 17:06.064
...since they started having them
before the Revolutionary War.

17:06.443 --> 17:09.105
It must be nice
to come from such an old family.

17:09.279 --> 17:13.443
All families are old, Sam.
Some just keep better records.

17:17.871 --> 17:20.283
Sam, hush that dog up.

17:20.457 --> 17:22.914
What are you doing
to get him so riled up?

17:24.461 --> 17:28.249
Mitch,
there's something's wrong with Sam.

17:34.179 --> 17:36.044
Lord in heaven.

17:40.810 --> 17:43.301
Sam. Sam.

17:43.480 --> 17:47.098
Don't put the red ones next to
the green ones. This ain't Christmas.

17:47.943 --> 17:50.525
Hey, get that dog out of here.

17:50.946 --> 17:53.904
Don’t shut me out, please.

17:56.826 --> 18:01.365
Georgia,
your replacement just showed up.

18:01.873 --> 18:04.865
"Thought you said
you were gonna get rid of her quick."

18:05.043 --> 18:08.160
Bitch, I love you, you scandalous whore.

18:08.338 --> 18:12.001
Take your man. Take his ass.

18:12.175 --> 18:13.676
--and company.

18:13.843 --> 18:16.676
Shut up. Shut up and get back upstairs.

18:16.846 --> 18:20.589
You better walk down them stairs like:

18:22.811 --> 18:27.054
Oh, I forgot to tell you, Georgia.
I saw the picture--

18:27.399 --> 18:30.311
Well, this an unexpected pleasure.

18:31.152 --> 18:33.859
EEEZ-‘i/E ,1: ~V< /.

18:36.950 --> 18:38.110
I can't stay long.

18:38.285 --> 18:43.245
Boyfriend, I can make you stay longer
than you ever thought you could.

18:43.415 --> 18:46.703
-Actually, I had something else in mind.
-What?

18:46.876 --> 18:51.290
-A little V-juice?
-Sold out.

18:55.135 --> 18:57.467
What? Ain't nothing I can do.

18:57.637 --> 19:02.131
My supplier only comes out after dark,
if you know what I mean.

19:02.309 --> 19:03.924
Damn it.

19:05.061 --> 19:08.849
-I have a speech tonight.
-You got stage fright?

19:09.566 --> 19:10.681
Yeah.

19:13.403 --> 19:15.894
I could help you with that.

19:18.074 --> 19:20.531
You know I can.

19:25.915 --> 19:27.746
I can't mess up my clothes.

19:28.585 --> 19:30.917
I love how Mamaw's Mudbugs
is exactly the same...

19:31.087 --> 19:34.750
...as when we used to go there
when I was little. Remember?

19:35.216 --> 19:38.959
Yeah, until I lost my license.

19:40.597 --> 19:44.181
First thing in the morning,
I'm going down to DMV.

19:46.269 --> 19:47.600
-What's wrong?
-I don't know.

19:47.771 --> 19:51.855
-Maybe one bucket was enough.
-I told you not to suck the heads.

19:52.025 --> 19:54.516
-Oh, good Lord in heaven.
-Hold on.

19:54.694 --> 19:57.857
I'll find us a drug store,
get you some Pepto.

20:05.955 --> 20:08.867
Excuse me.
What aisle's the Pepto-Bismol on?

20:09.042 --> 20:11.203
Aisle 7. Right over there.

20:12.128 --> 20:13.288
I know you.

20:15.340 --> 20:18.127
No, I'm sure you've mistaken me
for someone else.

20:18.301 --> 20:20.212
Miss Jeanette.

20:20.470 --> 20:22.210
No. I'm needed up front, ma'am.

20:22.389 --> 20:25.222
No, I know your face.
Don't run away from me.

20:25.392 --> 20:28.475
-Hey!
-You took advantage of my mama.

20:28.645 --> 20:31.728
-Don't touch me.
-Don't touch you? I ought to kill you, bitch.

20:31.898 --> 20:33.559
-I will call the police.
-Go ahead.

20:33.733 --> 20:37.646
Tell them how you charged me $800
to spit in my face and poison me.

20:37.821 --> 20:40.153
-You know what? I'll call them myself.
-Wait, wait.

20:40.323 --> 20:43.440
What was in that shit you gave me,
that snake juice?

20:44.411 --> 20:47.403
Ipecac syrup and a small amount of peyote.
It's perfectly safe.

20:47.580 --> 20:51.368
I puked my guts out.
I hallucinated stabbing a little girl.

20:51.543 --> 20:54.330
-What the fuck kind of person are you?
-Look.

20:54.504 --> 20:57.337
I got a son in prison,
another one in Iraq.

20:57.507 --> 21:01.591
I got a daughter with diabetes,
and three grandbabies I gotta take care of.

21:01.761 --> 21:06.130
I do what I have to for my family.
Same as you.

21:06.349 --> 21:08.556
I actually believed you had fixed me.

21:08.726 --> 21:10.762
Oh, my God,
I am such a fucking dumb-ass.

21:10.937 --> 21:12.393
Listen.

21:13.314 --> 21:17.273
Just because Miss Jeanette ain't real
doesn't mean she can't help people.

21:17.444 --> 21:19.901
You saw how it worked for your mama.

21:20.447 --> 21:22.028
She still sober?

21:22.198 --> 21:24.814
Once she finds out about you,
she'll be drinking again.

21:24.993 --> 21:26.858
Well, maybe she don't have to find out.

21:28.371 --> 21:30.703
Faith's a powerful thing.

21:32.584 --> 21:36.372
Fuck, fuck, fuck.

21:46.639 --> 21:48.504
-You get something for me?
-They're out.

22:51.788 --> 22:55.246
I'd ask you to dance, but I don't dance.

22:55.416 --> 22:57.907
Thanks anyhow, Terry.

22:58.086 --> 23:02.955
Sometimes, crowds makes me feel guilty
for not having fun like everyone else.

23:03.132 --> 23:05.748
And then I feel guilty for feeling guilty.

23:06.636 --> 23:09.218
Guilt is a useless emotion.

23:10.431 --> 23:12.808
Or so I've heard.

23:14.477 --> 23:16.308
I just wish Bill was here.

23:18.648 --> 23:22.641
There's some dead people
I wish was still around too.

23:43.131 --> 23:45.338
-I want it!
-Me!

23:51.347 --> 23:55.807
Idiot. You fed on a human
that belonged to another.

23:56.352 --> 23:58.809
Three months of starving
till your fangs grow back...

23:58.980 --> 24:01.517
...will teach you better manners.

24:01.691 --> 24:05.730
Brothers and sisters of the tribunal,
is this fair? Is this just?

24:05.903 --> 24:07.404
Yeah.

24:09.032 --> 24:13.867
Now, Luisa, the other one, please.
From the root.

24:29.510 --> 24:35.471
Sentence passed and executed.

24:35.642 --> 24:38.600
The trial is concluded. Best of luck.

24:38.770 --> 24:43.434
Moving on. This looks interesting.

24:43.775 --> 24:48.269
Eric Northman, sheriff of Area 5.

24:48.446 --> 24:51.358
-Magister.
-Well, then.

24:52.575 --> 24:54.406
Bring me your murderer.

25:20.645 --> 25:23.603
It's nice not to have to sneak it to you
no more, ain't it?

25:27.735 --> 25:32.445
-Yeah, it is surprising.
-See? I told you Amy wasn't a psycho.

25:32.615 --> 25:36.904
The more time you spend with us,
you'll see she's an amazing woman.

25:37.870 --> 25:39.610
What made her change her mind?

25:40.123 --> 25:44.332
Well, she wants you to live with us,
like part of the family.

25:44.502 --> 25:45.742
I do too.

25:47.463 --> 25:52.207
She tell you about
finding the Tru Bloods you brought me?

25:55.054 --> 25:56.669
You're lying.

25:58.391 --> 25:59.847
Well, what did she say?

26:00.017 --> 26:03.475
She said that withholding
was tantamount to lying...

26:03.646 --> 26:06.137
...and that your relationship
was better than that.

26:06.441 --> 26:07.897
Fuck.

26:09.068 --> 26:11.901
God, that even sounds like her.

26:12.071 --> 26:15.234
-She's playing you, Jason.
-No, she is not.

26:15.867 --> 26:17.823
Ain't nobody plays Jason Stackhouse.

26:17.994 --> 26:20.781
