bitch.

27:04.415 --> 27:09.876
Jason fucking Stackhouse,
you bigmouth motherfucker.

27:18.346 --> 27:21.088
Honey, let me set a spell.
I'm sweating all over this dress.

27:21.265 --> 27:25.884
What, you won't dance with me?
That's a fine thing at your own fais do-do.

27:26.312 --> 27:29.224
Go ask Sookie to dance.
The poor thing's got nobody here.

27:29.690 --> 27:31.817
Everyone's afraid of her.

27:32.360 --> 27:33.975
Go on.

27:39.325 --> 27:44.240
-Y'al| having a good time?
-You look lonely as a cloud. Ain't right.

27:44.413 --> 27:48.873
Why, thank you, Rene.
Arlene is a lucky lady.

27:50.878 --> 27:56.418
-Not everybody likes a coonass like me.
-I do. So does Bill.

27:58.427 --> 28:01.260
I don't have nothing against vampires,
you know that.

28:01.430 --> 28:05.764
But you're a good girl, Sookie.
I think you deserve better.

28:06.352 --> 28:08.263
Mind if I cut in?

28:14.902 --> 28:17.314
Okay, truce?

28:19.615 --> 28:22.277
It's not fair you being mad
about something I can't help.

28:22.451 --> 28:24.988
I'm mad that
you didn't trust me enough to tell me.

28:25.162 --> 28:27.369
You hid the most
important thing about yourself.

28:27.540 --> 28:29.952
So what? You're with Bill now.

28:30.126 --> 28:32.959
Yeah, and you're with Tara.
Another thing you didn't tell me.

28:33.129 --> 28:35.586
-There's nothing to tell.
-Oh, does she know that?

28:35.756 --> 28:40.625
-Or the fact that you can turn into a dog?
-It's none of her business.

28:41.637 --> 28:45.550
And you know what, I didn't tell you
because I knew this is how you'd react.

28:45.725 --> 28:47.807
But you're right. I didn't trust you.

28:47.977 --> 28:50.719
I trusted my instincts,
and they were dead-on.

28:54.317 --> 28:55.898
I think I'll get another beer.

28:56.068 --> 28:58.320
-Do you guys--? You want one?
-Oh, no.

28:58.487 --> 29:01.149
-Babe?
-Oh, no. I'm fine.

29:05.786 --> 29:08.994
You know, I think she's
my favorite girl you ever dated.

29:09.206 --> 29:13.119
-Where'd you meet her at?
-It's kind of embarrassing.

29:13.294 --> 29:14.374
Fangtasia.

29:14.545 --> 29:16.831
-What? The fuck you doing there?
-The vampire bar?

29:17.006 --> 29:20.965
The only reason I went there was because
there was this band playing that I like.

29:21.802 --> 29:25.135
You one brave motherfucker
going there to see them play.

29:25.306 --> 29:27.262
It's just a bunch of losers wearing black.

29:27.433 --> 29:30.675
Amy and I could tell by looking at
each other we didn't belong there.

29:30.853 --> 29:34.016
Then one thing sort of led to another.

29:35.441 --> 29:36.772
Never did see the band.

29:36.943 --> 29:40.982
-Oh, God, I wanna be you.
-So is this it?

29:41.155 --> 29:44.739
She the one who's gonna take Jason
Stackhouse off the market for good?

29:44.909 --> 29:46.774
I don't know.

29:47.995 --> 29:49.656
Now, what you waiting for?

29:49.830 --> 29:53.539
Life is short.
You find a good one, you keep her.

29:55.211 --> 30:00.251
You're right. I never felt this way
about any girl before.

30:00.841 --> 30:03.048
I think that's maybe why....

30:07.181 --> 30:10.799
I think I lost the upper hand
in the relationship, you know?

30:13.062 --> 30:14.427
VVhatsucks?

30:14.605 --> 30:16.106
-You take it back.
-Take it back?

30:16.273 --> 30:17.353
Take it back.

30:17.900 --> 30:20.437
You just say,
"Woman, this is what I want.

30:20.611 --> 30:22.272
This is the way it's gonna be."

30:22.446 --> 30:27.110
And if she don't like it, deep down she'll
respect you. She can't help it. It's her DNA.

30:28.077 --> 30:31.569
-Well, well, now I want to be you.
-Fuck you.

30:31.747 --> 30:33.578
Hey, and if she don't respect you?

30:33.749 --> 30:36.286
She ain't someone that
you wanna be with anyway.

30:37.003 --> 30:38.618
Okay?

30:39.755 --> 30:43.247
-He's right.
-|'ve been keeping an eye on you, Hoyt.

30:43.426 --> 30:47.590
That is your third beer,
and that is two too many.

30:47.763 --> 30:50.220
You set that down. Right now.

30:53.060 --> 30:56.803
You know, I plan on having
about six more beers.

30:56.981 --> 31:02.066
And enough tequila to drown
a Mexican sea captain, woman.

31:06.782 --> 31:08.773
Excuse me.

31:09.869 --> 31:13.111
Longshadow was choking the girl
and would have killed her.

31:13.289 --> 31:17.373
So you murdered a higher life form
for the sake of your pet.

31:17.543 --> 31:21.001
You broke an ancient
and fundamental law.

31:21.172 --> 31:25.165
You decreased our numbers
at a critical time in our history.

31:25.342 --> 31:26.798
Very bad.

31:26.969 --> 31:29.051
Very, very bad.

31:29.221 --> 31:33.555
Magister, Longshadow
broke the law first.

31:33.726 --> 31:35.216
She was mine and he knew it.

31:35.394 --> 31:39.637
-He would have killed her and fed from her.
-Hello, human.

31:39.815 --> 31:40.895
Irrelevant.

31:41.067 --> 31:42.773
Happens every day.

31:42.943 --> 31:44.228
He was stealing from Eric.

31:47.656 --> 31:48.782
Shenﬁ?

31:49.700 --> 31:51.156
Yes, Magister, it's true.

31:51.494 --> 31:53.325
Longshadow was a thief and a liar.

31:53.788 --> 31:55.153
He was hurting my business.

31:57.875 --> 32:02.164
The business part,
that is a serious offense.

32:02.338 --> 32:05.671
And it was the human
who exposed Longshadow.

32:05.841 --> 32:08.093
Would you tell him, Eric?

32:09.428 --> 32:12.044
The only reason the girl was there...

32:12.473 --> 32:13.804
...was because I called her.

32:14.183 --> 32:16.139
To protect your wealth.

32:16.310 --> 32:18.426
To protect my wealth, yes.

32:19.021 --> 32:22.855
Magister, she is...valuable.

32:23.025 --> 32:27.439
Humans exist to serve us.
That is their only value.

32:27.613 --> 32:30.525
There are those among us
who think differently.

32:32.660 --> 32:35.276
Do you question my authority?

32:35.996 --> 32:40.035
I am the Magister.
I was trained in the Inquisition...

32:40.209 --> 32:45.124
...and I am the adjudicator for every
vampire territory in North America.

32:45.297 --> 32:50.041
As the humans say, the humans
you love more than your own kind:

32:50.219 --> 32:52.005
Back your shit down.

32:53.222 --> 32:54.632
Bill.

33:03.065 --> 33:06.102
Well, you haven't bored me.

33:06.443 --> 33:09.059
That works in your favor.

33:10.573 --> 33:13.815
And you seem to be
obedient to your sheriff.

33:13.993 --> 33:16.029
For the most part.

33:19.290 --> 33:23.454
When it matters, yes, he is.

33:24.420 --> 33:29.756
The usual sentence is five years
in a coffin chained with silver.

33:29.925 --> 33:35.966
During which time your body
will waste to leather and sticks.

33:36.974 --> 33:40.091
You'll probably go insane.

33:41.604 --> 33:42.719
However...

33:45.024 --> 33:47.686
...I'm feeling a bit...

33:49.153 --> 33:50.734
...creative.

33:59.955 --> 34:03.072
You know what I love most about Rene?

34:03.250 --> 34:06.083
Aside from his fine little Cajun butt.

34:09.131 --> 34:10.632
He's good to the kids.

34:11.383 --> 34:13.635
He's good to me.

34:14.470 --> 34:17.132
All the rest were fixer-uppers.

34:17.681 --> 34:22.550
But Rene, he's solid
all the way to the foundation.

34:22.728 --> 34:25.014
I can count on him.

34:26.273 --> 34:29.811
And I've never had that in all my life.

34:30.611 --> 34:32.442
I know what you mean.

34:32.613 --> 34:35.980
I mean, I never knew I could have
something like what I have with Jason.

34:36.617 --> 34:39.154
I'm not about to let
anything destroy that.

34:39.703 --> 34:42.445
I don't know how anyone can
trust anybody these days.

34:42.623 --> 34:44.579
They're always keeping things from you.

34:44.750 --> 34:47.162
You don't even know who people are
or what they are.

34:52.675 --> 34:57.260
Well, you know what I love about Jason?
Everything is just right there on the surface.

34:57.429 --> 34:59.511
You never have to wonder
what he's thinking.

34:59.682 --> 35:01.593
Yeah, because he ain't thinking.

35:02.601 --> 35:07.015
-Hey, girlfriends, what's up?
-Tara, you look-- You look great.

35:07.523 --> 35:10.811
Prom night, 2000. I ain't wore it since.

35:10.985 --> 35:12.771
Well, it still fits you.

35:14.321 --> 35:16.232
Tara, come here.

35:17.199 --> 35:19.690
I've never seen you like this.
Is this because of Sam?

35:20.703 --> 35:22.284
I saw you. In his office.

35:22.454 --> 35:24.866
-Why didn't you tell me?
-It's none of your business.

35:25.040 --> 35:27.656
I'm just not sure that dating Sam
is such a good idea.

35:27.835 --> 35:29.700
Well, at least he doesn't drink my blood.

35:34.216 --> 35:37.299
SooMe.SooMe.

35:48.772 --> 35:52.105
-Oh, hey, Andy. You want a beer?
-I don't drink.

35:52.276 --> 35:53.812
Okay.

35:54.486 --> 35:56.397
Had me a very interesting conversation...

35:56.572 --> 35:59.063
...with a man at the naked community
over in Beaumont.

35:59.241 --> 36:01.323
That's right, I already told you.
Last night.

36:01.493 --> 36:04.826
Before you ran off to avoid talking to me.

36:05.456 --> 36:09.369
What's your story, Merlotte?
Who's your people?

36:10.919 --> 36:12.204
I was adopted.

36:12.588 --> 36:14.374
That's the truth.

36:14.882 --> 36:16.873
At 15, I was on my own.

36:17.634 --> 36:20.592
Fifteen, huh? Where'd you go?

36:21.013 --> 36:22.674
Who took you in?

36:22.848 --> 36:26.557
I need to know what your life was before
you bought up property in Bon Temps...

36:26.727 --> 36:29.264
...and women started getting killed.

36:50.751 --> 36:52.332
Mom?

37:11.438 --> 37:14.475
Sam. Sam.

37:17.653 --> 37:19.484
Where the hell did you come from?

37:19.655 --> 37:24.649
I come from exactly the same place
everybody else comes from, Andy.

37:24.827 --> 37:26.488
I been checking up on you.

37:26.662 --> 37:29.324
You got no records before
you moved here. Nothing.

37:29.498 --> 37:36.495
No taxes, no social security,
no credit card bills, no previous address.

37:36.672 --> 37:38.333
-Jesus fuck, Andy.
-Shit.

37:38.674 --> 37:42.667
Don't you ever get tired
of being in everybody's way?

37:42.845 --> 37:45.928
-I'm gonna have to pay for dry-cleaning.
-Hey, baby.

37:47.599 --> 37:51.512
Whoa, hey. Look at you.

37:52.187 --> 37:53.518
Listen.

37:54.106 --> 37:55.846
I have a situation.

37:56.024 --> 37:58.015
A very serious situation.

37:58.193 --> 38:01.105
And I need your help with it. Right now.

38:01.280 --> 38:03.111
I'm here on official police business...

38:03.282 --> 38:05.568
...and we're in the middle
of a conversation.

38:05.742 --> 38:07.949
Well, let me wrap it up for you.

38:08.120 --> 38:10.532
He doesn't know anything.
He didn't do anything.

38:10.706 --> 38:13.368
And he doesn't give a shit.

38:14.710 --> 38:16.541
Come on, Sam.

38:24.553 --> 38:26.043
How much have you had to drink?

38:26.221 --> 38:29.634
Quit acting like my damn boss
and just fuck me, please.

38:29.808 --> 38:31.469
Hey, did you have that exorcism?

38:31.643 --> 38:35.556
-Can't you be a normal guy and go with it?
-Because I'm not a normal guy.

38:35.731 --> 38:38.973
-Well, who the fuck cares?
-Damn it, Tara.

38:40.569 --> 38:44.357
I'm a person. I'm not a prop for you
to use every time you need to feel better.

38:44.656 --> 38:48.240
-Sam, please. I'm not right.
-You're not the only one with demons.

38:49.453 --> 38:52.160
Well, what the fuck
do you want from me?

38:55.209 --> 38:57.791
I don't want a goddamn thing from you.

38:57.961 --> 38:59.917
I don't want nothing from nobody.

39:23.237 --> 39:25.523
I told you to keep
your goddamn mouth shut.

39:25.697 --> 39:28.109
Hey. This is my good shirt.

39:28.283 --> 39:29.784
And yeah, I kept my mouth shut.

39:29.952 --> 39:33.536
My supplier, he gone.
He fucking missing.

39:33.705 --> 39:36.788
If other vampires find out I been selling,
the same shit is gonna--

39:36.959 --> 39:39.325
You understand?
The same shit is gonna happen to me.

39:40.963 --> 39:42.874
You got nothing to worry about.

39:43.048 --> 39:47.417
Bitch, you think life is just this one
fucking game that you always win...

39:47.594 --> 39:50.961
...no matter how many dead folk
are piling up around you.

39:51.807 --> 39:55.470
Maudette. Dawn. Your grandma.

39:55.644 --> 39:59.557
And I tell you one fucking thing:
I ain't gonna be next, bitch.

39:59.731 --> 40:03.724
On my mama grave, motherfucker.
I ain't gonna be next.

40:03.902 --> 40:05.984
FucMnguu

40:16.582 --> 40:18.948
You have no nest.

40:19.126 --> 40:21.993
You prefer to consort with humans.

40:22.921 --> 40:26.630
You seem to have lost
all sense of our priorities.

40:27.175 --> 40:33.341
William Compton, you owe us a life.

40:36.518 --> 40:38.019
No.

40:57.581 --> 40:59.037
No.

41:01.293 --> 41:05.127
Oh, precious Jesus,
God, save me, save me.

41:05.297 --> 41:06.707
Make it all a dream.

41:11.178 --> 41:13.464
Put me in the coffin, Magister.

41:13.639 --> 41:17.348
-I will go willingly.
-Please, it's the first time I ever snuck out.

41:20.520 --> 41:23.887
I only ever get to go to youth choir
and prayer group.

41:24.066 --> 41:27.149
You take me home, I won't say a word
to Mama and Daddy or anybody.

41:27.319 --> 41:30.152
Please, please, just please help me.

41:30.781 --> 41:33.363
There's no help for you, child.

41:41.958 --> 41:44.085
Meet your Maker.

41:52.386 --> 41:54.342
